---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Federica Fanì"
  description="Pescara, Macerata, Rome. Piano, drums, vinyl, code. The long version is here."
  lang="en"
>

  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-inner">
      <div class="about-hero-left">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow reveal">
          <span class="eyebrow-line"></span>
          <span class="eyebrow">About me</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
          Piano and drums.<br>
          Vinyl and code.<br>
          <em>The long version.</em>
        </h1>
        <p class="about-hero-sub reveal reveal-delay-2">
          Pescara, Macerata, Rome. Three cities, three different energies, one person who carried a piece of each.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-hero-right reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="about-img-wrap">
          <img src="/images/foto.png" alt="Federica Fanì" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-dark">
    <section class="section">
      <div class="sec-header">
        <div class="sec-header-left">
          <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light reveal">The basics</span>
          <h2 class="sec-title-light reveal reveal-delay-1">The essentials</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="basi-grid">
        <div class="basi-item reveal">
          <div class="basi-label">Born in</div>
          <div class="basi-text">Pescara, 1996. Grew up there, then spent a few years in Macerata, then Rome from 2022. Three cities with three completely different energies — and I brought a piece of each one with me.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="basi-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="basi-label">Languages</div>
          <div class="basi-text">Italian, English (with a British accent I can't quite explain), Spanish and French. Useful both professionally and for misunderstanding song lyrics in creative ways.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="basi-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="basi-label">Tattoos</div>
          <div class="basi-text">19, mostly music-related. Five are dedicated to Paramore, and no, it's not a phase.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="basi-item reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="basi-label">Main obsession</div>
          <div class="basi-text">Vinyl records. Not a hobby — a philosophy.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="basi-item reveal">
          <div class="basi-label">Book I recommend to everyone</div>
          <div class="basi-text">
            <em>The Enchantress of Numbers</em> by Jennifer Chiaverini, about the life of Ada Lovelace, widely regarded as the first programmer in history. Fictional, but beautifully written. If you want to explore who Ada was and the broader story of women in STEM history, <a href="https://www.salamandersgarden.com/donne-stem-storia-dati-e-un-pizzico-di-speranza/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="basi-link">I wrote something on it too</a>.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="basi-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="basi-label">Favourite game</div>
          <div class="basi-text">RDR2 or Cyberpunk 2077, depending on my mood. Melancholic cowboy or cyberpunk hacker. Opposites, again.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="basi-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="basi-label">Evening wind-down method</div>
          <div class="basi-text">Stardew Valley with a history podcast in the background. Simultaneously. More effective than any guided meditation.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="section timeline-section" id="about">
    <div class="sec-header">
      <div class="sec-header-left">
        <span class="eyebrow reveal">The timeline</span>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">How I got here</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="tl-item reveal">
        <div class="tl-year">1996</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">Born in Pescara. A memorable event according to my parents. According to me, the beginning of a long series of their questionable musical decisions.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="tl-year">2002</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">My parents take me to a piano teacher they knew. Official reason: "you can't play any instrument without learning piano first." Real reason, discovered years later: the teacher didn't play drums and couldn't teach them. Fair enough. I learn piano — and honestly, I've never regretted it.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="tl-year">2005</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">I discover Paramore. It's not a phase.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal">
        <div class="tl-year">2010/2011</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">At 14/15 I remember I always wanted to play drums. My mother is horrified — the piano had already "ruined" the living room, as far as she was concerned. Spoiler: there's now an acoustic drum kit in the same room. She lost.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="tl-year">Around the same time</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">Tumblr introduces me to code. Like most teenagers of the era, I start tinkering with HTML and CSS to customise my blog. I didn't know it yet, but I had just started programming.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="tl-year">10 June 2013</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">First Paramore concert, Milan. Incredible energy, the emotion of finally seeing your favourite band live. One of the best shows I've ever been to.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal">
        <div class="tl-year">2020/2021</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">During lockdown I discover Luca La Mesa's courses and get into social media management. I find a passion I didn't know I had. I haven't stopped since.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="tl-year">2022</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">I move to Rome. Third city, third energy, first time I feel like I'm exactly where I'm supposed to be.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="tl-year">Today</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-text">I manage social media profiles, build Flutter apps, study two degrees at once because apparently I enjoy suffering, collect vinyl, and occasionally go cycling to get body and mind moving at the same speed. Opposites don't cancel each other out — they multiply.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-dark">
    <section class="section cta-section">
      <div class="cta-inner">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light reveal">Let's talk</span>
        <h2 class="sec-title-light reveal reveal-delay-1">Got a project in mind?</h2>
        <p class="cta-sub reveal reveal-delay-2">Messages don't bite. Write to me for collaborations, projects, or just to recommend an album.</p>
        <div class="cta-btns reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <a href="/en/contatti" class="btn btn-gold">Get in touch</a>
          <a href="/en/servizi" class="btn btn-outline-light">Explore services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

</Layout>
